imes'' 17 Dec 1942: 46.</ref>\n* ''Clementina'' by [[A.E.W. Mason]] (1942)<ref>\"While the Films Reel By\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 11 Jan 1942: C3.</ref>\n* ''[[When Knighthood Was in Flower (1942 film)|When Knighthood Was in Flower]]'' (1942)\n* ''But Is It Love'' (1942) with [[Carole Lombard]]<ref>\"Charles Laughton to Appear in 'The History of Mr. Polly' \u2013 Role for James Craig: Roxy Film in Third Week \u2013 'Remember the Day' Held Over \u2013 'Girl From Leningrad' Remains at Stanley\". ''New York Times'' 9 Jan 1942: 25.</ref>\n* ''The Raft'' (1943) with [[William Bendix]]<ref name=\"cary\">\"New 'Monte Cristo' Feature Announced John Garfield, John Ridgely Will Join Cary Grant in 'Destination Tokyo'\". Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 18 June 1943: 15.</ref>\n* ''The Guy from Mike's Place'' (1943)<ref>\"Looking at Hollywood\" Hopper, Hedda. ''Chicago Daily Tribune'' 27 July 1943: 15.</ref>\n* ''The Notorious Nancy Gray'' (1943)<ref>\"Sanders Wins Key Role in 'Dorian Gray' Film Producer Small Seeks Stellar Songstress for Musical, 'Notorious Nancy Grazy'\". Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 28 Dec 1943: 7.</ref>\n* ''Big Time'' (1943) with [[Ed Wynn]]<ref name=\"cary\"/>\n* remake of ''[[Two Arabian Knights]]'' (1944) with Dennis O'Keefe and William Bendix<ref>\"O'Keefe Pressuring Small to Do 'Knights': Pressburger Will Route 'The Blivens' First to Stage, Then to Picture Medium\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 1 Feb 1944: 9.</ref>\n* remake of ''Are You a Mason?'' (1944)<ref name=\"Times19440625\">Hollywood Awakens to the Shorts: One and Two Reel Films Regaining Popularity \u2013 Love Wins as Usual. Fred Standley. ''New York Times'' 25 June 1944: X3.</ref>\n* ''When the Cat's Away'' (1944)<ref>\"News of the Screen\" ''The Christian Science Monitor'' 21 July 1944: 4.</ref>\n* ''Two Yanks in Paris'' (1945) \u2013 sequel to ''[[Abroad with Two Yanks]]''<ref>\"Comedy Yanks Plan Entry Into Paris, Too: Topical 'First Man in Tokyo' Scheduled; Marsha Hunt Joins Garson Entourage\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 28 Aug 1944: 8.</ref>\n* ''A Time to be Born'' (1945) from book by [[Dawn Powell]]<ref name=\"screen\"/>\n* ''Lucretia Borgia'' (1945)<ref name=\"screen\"/>\n* ''D'Artagnan'' (1945)<ref name=\"screen\"/>\n* adaptation of ''[[The Scarlet Letter]]'' (1946)<ref>\"Small Plans Classic; Quints Deal Hovers\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 29 Mar 1946: A7.</ref>\n* ''Kate Fennigate'' (1946) from novel by [[Booth Tarkington]]<ref>\"Filmland Briefs\". ''Los Angeles Times'' 23 May 1946: A3.</ref>\n* ''The O'Flynn'' (1946)<ref>\"Stage's Vye Will Vie With Academy Winner\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 28 June 1946: A3.</ref>\n* ''The Treasure of Monte Cristo'' (1948)<ref>\"Small Plans Film on 'Monte Cristo': Seeks Louis Hayward for Lead in Movie on Dumas Hero \u2013 Beloin Doing Hope Script\". Thomas F. Brady. ''New York Times'' 15 June 1948: 33.</ref>\n* ''Twelve Against the Underworld'' (1948) for [[Eagle Lion]]<ref name=\"twelve\"/>\n* ''Crime on the Waterfront'' (1948) based on a series of newspaper articles<ref name=\"brady\"/>\n* ''The Los Angeles Story'' (1948) based on a script by [[Philip Yordan]]<ref name=\"brady\"/>\n* remake of ''[[The Sheik (film)|The Sheik]]'' (1950)<ref>\"Mitchell Likely Cap'n Andy; Preston to Star as Heavy With Rooney\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 22 Aug 1950: A11.</ref>\n* ''Far West'' (1953) with producer Arthur Hornblow written by Sonya Levien<ref>\"Sobbin' Women' Shaping for Betta St. John; 'Far West' Set for Hornblow\" Schallert, Edwin. ''Los Angeles Times'' 6 Mar 1953: B7.</ref>\n* ''Cannibal Island'' (1953) a historical adventure tale with [[Lex Barker]]<ref>\"Looking at Hollywood: Olivia de Havilland Off This Week for Europe\" Hopper, Hedda. ''Chicago Daily Tribune'' 2 Apr 1953: c5.</ref>\n* ''The Mad Magician'' (1953)<ref>\"Looking at Hollywood: Fernando Lamas' Next Film in Busy Season Is 'Honeymoon'\" Hopper, Hedda. 