{"title_page": "Edward Corrie (tennis)", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n| name                  = Edward Corrie\n| fullname              = Edward Martin Corrie<ref name=\"Search 1984 to 2006 - Birth, Marriage and Death indexes\">{{cite web\n| title = Search 1984 to 2006 \u2013 Birth, Marriage and Death indexes\n| url = http://www.findmypast.com/post84BMDSearchStart.action?redef=0&searchType=B\n| publisher = Findmypast.com\n| accessdate = 13 June 2013}}</ref>\n| image                 = Edward Corrie 2, 2015 Wimbledon Qualifying - Diliff.jpg\n| country               = {{flagicon|Great Britain}} [[Great Britain]]\n| birth_date            = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|2|21}}\n| birth_place           = [[Hatfield, Hertfordshire|Hatfield]], England\n| turnedpro             = 2005\n| retired               = 2018\n| careerprizemoney      = [[US$|$]]219,337\n| singlesrecord         = 0\u20131\n| singlestitles         = 0\n| highestsinglesranking = No. 215 (13 October 2014)\n| Wimbledonresult       = Q3 ([[2016 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles Qualifying|2016]])\n| doublesrecord               = 0\u20132\n| doublestitles               = 0\n| highestdoublesranking       = No. 142 (10 November 2014)\n| WimbledonDoublesresult      = 1R ([[2014 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Doubles|2014]], [[2015 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Doubles|2015]])\n| updated               = 1 October 2018\n}}\n'''Edward Martin Corrie''' (born 21 February 1988) is a former British [[tennis]] player.\n\n==Career==\nCorrie played collegiately at the [[University of Texas at Austin]] from 2007 to 2011.<ref>https://texassports.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2506</ref> He made his debut on the [[ITF Men's Circuit]] in 2005, and since then has won 27 Futures tournaments: seven in singles and twenty in doubles. He has also won two [[ATP Challenger Tour|ATP Challenger]] doubles tournaments.\n\nHe was primarily a doubles player until achieving success in singles in 2013, earning him a wildcard to the main draw of the [[2013 Aegon Championships \u2013 Singles|2013 Queen's Club Championships]], losing his first round match 4\u20136, 6\u20137<sup>(1)</sup> to [[Sergiy Stakhovsky]], ranked 116th.\n\nCorrie announced his retirement from tennis in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ed Corrie retires after 20 years dedication to tennis. - Herts Tennis |url=http://hertstennis.co.uk/2018/07/25/ed-corrie-retires-20-years-dedication-tennis/ |website=Herts Tennis |date=25 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career finals==\n\n===Singles: 22 (7\u201315)===\n{|\n|-valign=top\n|\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:97%\n!Legend (Singles)\n|-bgcolor=e5d1cb\n|-bgcolor=moccasin\n|ATP Challenger Tour (0\u20131)\n|-bgcolor=cffcff\n|ITF Futures Tour (7\u201314)\n|}\n|\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:97%\n!Titles by Surface\n|-\n|Hard (7\u201313)\n|-\n|Clay (0\u20130)\n|-\n|Grass (0\u20131)\n|-\n|Carpet (0\u20131)\n|}\n|}\n\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n!Result\n!class=\"unsortable\"|W\u2013L\n!{{ns}}Date{{ns}}\n!Tournament\n!Tier\n!Surface\n!Opponent\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-\n|bgcolor=FFA07A|Loss\n|<small>0\u20131</small>\n|{{dts|Aug 2011}}\n|style=\"background:#cffcff;\"|Great Britain F12, [[Roehampton]]\n|style=\"background:#cffcff;\"|Futures\n|Hard\n|{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Jamie Baker (tennis)|Jamie Baker]]\n|1\u20136, 6\u20134, 1\u20136\n|-\n|bgcolor=FFA07A|Loss\n|<small>0\u20132</small>\n|{{dts|Jul 2012}}\n|style=\"background:#cffcff;\"|Great Britain F10, [[Ilkley]]\n|style=\"background:#cffcff;\"|Futures\n|Grass\n|{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Josh Goodall]]\n|4\u20136, 1\u20136\n|-\n|bgcolor=98FB98|Win\n|<small>1\u20132</small>\n|{{dts|Jan 2013}}\n|style=\"background:#cffcff;\"|Great Britain F2, [[Preston, Lancashire|Preston]]\n|style=\"background:#cffcff;\"|Futures\n|Hard (i)\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Christian Harrison]]\n|2\u20136, 6\u20133, 7\u20135\n|-\n|bgcolor=FFA07A|Loss\n|<small>1\u20133</small>\n|{{dts|Feb 20